<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-07-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-07-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="702" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d702">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Merry</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">San
                                        Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-07-17"><hi rend="italic">July 17,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Merry reports that arrangement of armistice for Wednesday—to-morrow
                            morning—is made and that the <hi rend="italic">Marblehead</hi> is
                            expected to arrive at San Jose de Guatemala from Acajutla Thursday
                            morning to receive all commissioners. Inquires whether he shall
                            represent Costa Rica and Nicaragua, as requested, Combs being absent,
                            Brown to substitute.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>